metadata.name: PORTALS #67
metadata.description:
Interactive 3D scenes coded with love in Babylon.js
Please explore and play with your mouse. Discover different sounds hidden in different parts of the scene.
 
-8 Random Escape Portals. Each of the Portals contains an animated material Driven by a Graphic Shader that changes over time.
- The color combinations were cut up and put into a list.
- Each of the characters moves in back and forth animations in this Interactive 3d Experience.

CONTROLS:
Click >> sound On!
Left click >> rotate >> rotate
Scroll up / down >> zoom >> zoom

metadata.name: Truchet Towers #67
metadata.description:
Curved Truchet tiling is laid down on a 3D plane forming an imaginary landscape of ripples.

The longest continuous line created by the tiling is removed, cutting a path through the terrain.
This occurs within 3D space and may or may not appear within the confines of the canvas frame,
but most likely will appear.

A tower rises up to wherever a circle is created by the tiling. Driven by the random
tiling, zero or several of these may appear within the frame. Shadows differ in each mint.

In addition to working on decorative tiling, Sébastien Truchet worked on canals and sundials,
forming the inspiration for the exploration of shade and shadow in this work.

Mints will have a variety of earth-tone background colors with each perspective of the scene
slightly different to produce diverse results.

As I researched Sébastien Truchet I learned that he worked with hydraulics and canal design,
as well as sundials. This became the inspiration for my new shading and shadowing technique used
in this piece.

For me this piece evokes a sense of agriculture, and connects me to an imaginary
landscape that could have looked familiar to Truchet in 18th century France.

This work was created with my own javascript, utilizing my polyline path helper library I
maintain at https://github.com/markroland/path-helper.

metadata.name: ROMA #133
metadata.description:
Roma is a generative and animated piece creating shapes based on trails.  The size, position and amplitude of each lines are generated for each token, along with the color theme. Some rare items are available.

Each reloading creates a different movement, as the algorithm underlying the piece is partially based on a noise.

At the end, the animation stop and the visual is created.

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Roma (Italia).

metadata.name: Soil Horizon #118
metadata.description:
A Soil horizon is a layer parallel to the soil surface whose physical, chemical, and biological characteristics differ from the layers above and beneath. 

Horizons are defined in many cases by obvious physical features, mainly color and texture.

Coded with p5js by @LESSLIE
___

Click the Open Live button
Press [S] to save the high-resolution version

May 2022

metadata.name: Chaos Machine Part 1 #6
metadata.description:
This work of generative art explores the transitional and interactive spaces between determinism and randomness, between chaos and order, between human and computer, between surface and essence, and between artist and audience. 

Enjoy the art at the aesthetic level as it is generated by algorithm and chance, but also look deeper, explore, and see what u might discover.

Secondary royalties from this piece will be split with the original minter, and ownership of this piece will inform the access list for future related works.

metadata.name: Generative Charts #02 #317
metadata.description:
Click and drag to adjust camera. Hover on points to view data.

Each 3d chart has a set of unique features:
- 14 cryptocurrency tokens
- 7 date ranges
- 6 variables visualized (variable 1)
- 6 variables visualized (variable 2)
- 5 line types
- 7 opacity settings
- many colors

Once a unique chart is created it will keep evolving with the latest data every time it is viewed. One point per day. Uses The Graph Sushiswap data (https://thegraph.com/explorer/subgraph?id=0x4bb4c1b0745ef7b4642feeccd0740dec417ca0a0-0). 

Real live data is visualized, hover on points for info.

⚠️ highly experimental ⚠️

metadata.name: (un)existing #188
metadata.description:
The existing nature grows on the unexisting spirits.

Generative sketch, based on the pen and ink drawings of Po Sheng Chen. Po Sheng Chen is an Architect who has drawn nothing but Architecture for over 25 years. He tried to explore something different from his previous style (Brutalism with Magical Realism), so developed his own Minimalist Architecture process and style. After breaking up all the complicated elements and symbols, he chose a simple and naive way to present “pure volumes in the space (the essential of Architecture)”: the Use of different densities of vertical lines to create different faces of volumes, with the addition of horizontal lines to create shadows on the volumes. Shadow determined the form of volumes, then they became a clear composition in the space, Eliminating chaos. These lines seem like spirits to Po Sheng Chen, because they represent the soul of Architecture, but they do not have a specific form or meaning...they are between existing and unexisting! Tezumie is a creative generative artist. He saw the latest experimental drawings of Po Sheng Chen, and after reaching out, the collab was formed with the goal of creating a digital representation of the original concept surrounded by a natural and overgrown environment. The combination of nature and architecture.

Made in p5js.

metadata.name: Horizon #92
metadata.description:
Horizon is made in the technique of "pointing". Each line consists of hundreds of dots.

Variations:

- 40% night and moon / 60% sun
- 30% colored lines. In this case you get unpredictable combinations. For example, a green moon and pink trees.
- 40% pier / 60% shore
- if there is a pier, 75% that there will be a tent on it
- different types of framing
- 15% singleton background and black lines

Please see variations.

______
by neigal 02.05.2022

metadata.name: Layered Landscapes #64
metadata.description:
Layered Landscapes explores representing imaginary landscapes through line art designed for output with a pen plotter.

It supports these variations:

Hill Contours: 4 layers
Dark Foreground: 50% chance the first contour is overprinted for darker darks
Sky: straight or curved
fog: 0, 1 or 2 layers
trees: 1 to 7

Press "s" to download the SVG.

Output is designed for 6" x 4".
